<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q11_v3" title="Q11_v3" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="multiple" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceC</qti-value>
      <qti-value>ChoiceD</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="2">
      <qti-prompt>Ana tiene <m:math><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:math> pesos y gasta <m:math><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn></m:math> pesos en una compra. Ella afirma que ha gastado el <m:math><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math> de su dinero. ¿Cuáles de las siguientes afirmaciones permiten justificar lo que dice Ana?</qti-prompt>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">Que <m:math><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>25&#160;000</m:mn></m:math>.</qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">Que <m:math><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn></m:math>, <m:math><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:math> y <m:math><m:mn>25&#160;000</m:mn></m:math> son múltiplos de <m:math><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn></m:math>.</qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">Que <m:math><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn></m:math> es divisor de <m:math><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:math>.</qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">Que la fracción del dinero que gastó, <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math>, es equivalente a <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math>.</qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>

    <qti-feedback-block identifier="FB_CORRECT" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Correcto.</strong></p>
        <p>Las alternativas C y D permiten justificar lo que dice Ana.</p>
        <p>Por una parte, si <m:math><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn></m:math> es divisor de <m:math><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:math>, entonces <m:math><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>÷</m:mo><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:math>, así que <m:math><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn></m:math> es la cuarta parte de <m:math><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:math>.</p>
        <p>Por otra parte, <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math>.</p>
        <p>Por lo tanto, Ana gastó el <m:math><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math> de su dinero.</p>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>

    <qti-feedback-block identifier="FB_ONLY_C" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Parcialmente correcto.</strong></p>
        <p>La alternativa C sí permite justificar lo que dice Ana, porque <m:math><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>÷</m:mo><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:math>, de modo que <m:math><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn></m:math> es la cuarta parte de <m:math><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:math>, y una cuarta parte corresponde a <m:math><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math>.</p>
        <p>Sin embargo, faltó marcar la alternativa D, que también es válida, porque muestra directamente que <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math> es equivalente a <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math>.</p>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>

    <qti-feedback-block identifier="FB_ONLY_D" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Parcialmente correcto.</strong></p>
        <p>La alternativa D sí permite justificar lo que dice Ana, porque <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math>.</p>
        <p>Sin embargo, faltó marcar la alternativa C, que también es válida, porque si <m:math><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn></m:math> es divisor de <m:math><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:math>, entonces <m:math><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn></m:math> es la cuarta parte de <m:math><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:math>, y eso corresponde a <m:math><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math>.</p>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>

    <qti-feedback-block identifier="FB_A" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Incorrecto.</strong></p>
        <p>La igualdad <m:math><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>25&#160;000</m:mn></m:math> es verdadera, pero no justifica qué fracción del dinero inicial gastó Ana.</p>
        <p>Para justificar el <m:math><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math> se debe relacionar lo gastado con el total: <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math>.</p>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>

    <qti-feedback-block identifier="FB_B" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Incorrecto.</strong></p>
        <p>Es cierto que <m:math><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn></m:math>, <m:math><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:math> y <m:math><m:mn>25&#160;000</m:mn></m:math> son múltiplos de <m:math><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn></m:math>, pero eso no basta para justificar que lo gastado corresponde al <m:math><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math> del dinero inicial.</p>
        <p>La justificación correcta debe mostrar que la parte gastada respecto del total es <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math> y que esa fracción equivale a <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math>.</p>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>

    <qti-feedback-block identifier="FB_MIXED" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Respuesta incorrecta.</strong></p>
        <p>Las afirmaciones que justifican lo que dice Ana son C y D.</p>
        <p>En efecto, <m:math><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>÷</m:mo><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:math>, por lo que <m:math><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn></m:math> es la cuarta parte de <m:math><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:math>. Además, <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math>.</p>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>

    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Identificar el total y la parte gastada</strong></p>
            <p>Ana tenía <m:math><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:math> pesos en total y gastó <m:math><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn></m:math> pesos.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Escribir la fracción que representa lo gastado</strong></p>
            <p>La fracción del dinero que gastó es:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Simplificar la fracción</strong></p>
            <p>Dividimos numerador y denominador por <m:math><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn></m:math>:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mrow><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>÷</m:mo><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>÷</m:mo><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Relacionar la fracción con el porcentaje</strong></p>
            <p>Sabemos que:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math></p>
            <p>Entonces:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 5: Interpretar la opción C</strong></p>
            <p>Si <m:math><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn></m:math> es divisor de <m:math><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn></m:math>, entonces <m:math><m:mn>20&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>÷</m:mo><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:math>. Por eso, <m:math><m:mn>5&#160;000</m:mn></m:math> corresponde a una de 4 partes iguales del total, es decir, a <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math>, que equivale a <m:math><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>Las alternativas C y D justifican correctamente lo que dice Ana, porque ambas permiten concluir que la parte gastada es <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math> del total, es decir, <m:math><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>

  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-correct identifier="RESPONSE"/>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_CORRECT</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>

      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-and>
          <qti-match>
            <qti-container-size>
              <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
            </qti-container-size>
            <qti-base-value base-type="integer">1</qti-base-value>
          </qti-match>
          <qti-member>
            <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
            <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          </qti-member>
        </qti-and>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ONLY_C</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>

      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-and>
          <qti-match>
            <qti-container-size>
              <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
            </qti-container-size>
            <qti-base-value base-type="integer">1</qti-base-value>
          </qti-match>
          <qti-member>
            <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
            <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          </qti-member>
        </qti-and>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ONLY_D</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>

      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-and>
          <qti-match>
            <qti-container-size>
              <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
            </qti-container-size>
            <qti-base-value base-type="integer">1</qti-base-value>
          </qti-match>
          <qti-member>
            <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
            <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          </qti-member>
        </qti-and>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_A</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>

      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-and>
          <qti-match>
            <qti-container-size>
              <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
            </qti-container-size>
            <qti-base-value base-type="integer">1</qti-base-value>
          </qti-match>
          <qti-member>
            <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
            <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          </qti-member>
        </qti-and>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_B</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>

      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_MIXED</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>